<br>
There's this strip club on 5th Ave that sometimes has 50cent beer happy hours.  You walk by one day to check if they have the special but it's too late and the beers are back to the normal price of $6 a pop.  You feel horny as shit though so you go in to see some T&amp;A.  On the way out you run into your mom and dad on the street.<br>
<br>
Pops looks at you and asks what you are doing in Club PootiTang and you respond by saying that you don't need to go to a club to see naked women cause you have Kyrana at home.  The old man doesn't buy it for a second and asks, &quot;So why were you in there?&quot;  To which you respond that you go there for the cheap drinks.  Pops looks at the sign that says happy hour is over and take a guess as to what he's thinking eh?<br>
<br>
Back to the topic at hand.  You say:<br>
<br>
&quot;The quote you have listed there is me TRYING to explain to them that there's no reason for me to lie about the SMR, because I realistically have little to gain from it, and EVEN IF one actually DID drop, there's no way in hell I'm giving it to them. Understand?&quot;<br>
<br>
Umm no I don't understand.  You say even if it dropped you would keep it, so how does whether or not you NEED the SMR affect what benefit you get about lying?  You'd keep it either way.  I am guessing that this logic is too much for you so I'll break it down even further into two situations:<br>
<br>
A) You don't need the SMR.  The SMR drops.  You keep it.  Regardless of if you say it drops or not,you keep it.<br>
<br>
B) You DO need the SMR.  The SMR drops.  You keep it.  Regardless of if you say it drops or not, you keep it.<br>
<br>
Whether you NEED the SMR or not doesn't affect at all what you get out of lying about the drop.  Yet you claim that you said you didn't need the SMR in order to show you weren't lying.  The one has nothing to do with the other.  IMHO it's just a lame attempt to cover up the truth, which is that for some unknown reason you couldn't come out and say that you wanted an SMR and that's why you killed the AM when Maniak asked.<br>
<br>
Even after all that, there is the possibility that you weren't intentionally lying but did so because of a lack of mental faculty.  But wait, there's more...  You follow it up by saying you were in the AM room to powerlevel.  He's not asking HOW you knew the AM was up.  He's asking why you were in the room.  You were in the room to kill the AM.  Easy enough to say that, but instead you say you were there to powerlevel.  WHO exactly are you powerlevelling when you kill the mob on your own and get the xp?  Referring back to the analogy, how the hell are you in there for 50cent beers when they're only serving $6 draft?  <br>
